result.execSummary:
Dion James Gresham was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Dion James Gresham was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: NOT HELD. Needed to enter in order to close the case.

3:18 Defendant Dion James Gresham in court, in custody.  Sean Edward Froelich appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Constitutional rights explained to defendant.    Exam'd re: understanding of law, penalty and rights. Def waives his right and will willingly return to the State of Minnesota. Def asks when the State of Minnesota has to come get him. Court: if it's not done in a reasonable amount of time; Def may ask for a bail hearing. Statute states "forth with"...couple days. Def signs Waiver of Extradition form. Court signs order.
